{"id":14880816,"mediaExerciseId":"13e48e44-e47d-4c36-b7d5-67d2abcbc260","exerciseName":"21","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":87,"solutions":[{"id":6056120,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Here we are required to interpret a statement from a groceries chain advertising campaign. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following data:\n\n*In millions*\n\n\nFrom the statement:\n\n|Child||\n|--|--|\nIncome from the trip| $1.50\nMoney for the groceries| $50\n\nAlso, we will consider the table provided.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The argument comes from a comparison of the Profit Margin from both activities. \n\n$$ \\text{Profit Margin} = \\frac{\\text{Net Income}}{\\text{Sales}}\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The grocery chain:\n\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned} \n\\text{Profit Margin} &= \\frac{\\$10.2}{\\$680}\\\\\n &= \\boxed{0.015}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe Profit Margin for the grocery chain is **0.015**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"For the case of the child we interpret the income from the trip as the Net Income and the money for the groceries as the sales:\n\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned} \n\\text{Profit Margin} &= \\frac{\\$1.5}{\\$50}\\\\\n &= \\boxed{0.030}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe Profit Margin for the grocery chain is **0.030**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we can argue that claim is made on the basis that the Profit Margin from their activity [the grocery chaim] is half from that of the child doing groceries. \n\nHowever, we can say that this is misleading and exagerated since the volume of money produced by the grocery store is significantly higher than that of the child. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"53fee260-a362-4b7b-bc1f-0ec58c7aabf2","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880817,"exerciseName":"22","page":87,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a6437864-2486-48e1-8a32-4fed94006cb5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-22-a6437864-2486-48e1-8a32-4fed94006cb5"},{"id":14880818,"exerciseName":"23","page":87,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5864a723-1a7a-4c4b-a047-859313e903e9","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-23-5864a723-1a7a-4c4b-a047-859313e903e9"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880815,"exerciseName":"20","page":8